Using all the record fingers except current testing finger as test set, match the template of current finger and test set fingers one by one, if the match is successful, it is considered a FAR.
Using the real samples of current finger as test set, match the template of current finger and test set fingers one by one, if the match fails, it is considered a FLRR.
Using the samples of current finger as test set, match the template of current finger and test set fingers one by one, if the match fails, it is considered a FRR.
Using the fake samples of current finger as test set, match the template of current finger and test set fingers one by one, if the match is successful, it is considered a FSAR.
Using the fake samples of all recorded fingers as test set, match the template of current finger and test set fingers one by one, if the match is successful, it is considered a SCR.
